      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ZEMGRINDA (1) was quickly back on track, just missing in a 66 this trip at Caulfield Heath and then was caught wide from the outside barrier at Wangaratta and forgive. Apprentice Emily Pozman has won three times on the gelding and is reunited. Has been kept on the fresh side and should enjoy a softer run. Well placed to win. FOXY HEART (5) has needed racing but got to within 2.6L at Geelong second-up. Draws much better today and will find this grade more suitable. Has more to give and has to be considered. LEXTON (3) resumes and is proven fresh. Has pieces of form good enough for this and has jumped out well. The betting will be key. FROSTY NIGHT (7) is a leader who saluted at Edenhope two runs ago, and then held that level of form beaten 1.8L at Terang. Has her share of ability and is in the mix. OLIVIA'S SCANDAL (6) draws better today and will be around the mark.",
